article.description: Devonte Patterson had 27 points and grabbed 14 rebounds as Prairie View won its seventh straight home game, topping Texas Southern 69-59 on Saturday.
article.headline: Prairie View A&M adds to streak, beats Texas Southern 69-59
article.linkText: Prairie View A&M adds to streak, beats Texas Southern 69-59
article.story: PRAIRIE VIEW, Texas -- Devonte Patterson had 27 points and grabbed 14 rebounds as Prairie View won its seventh straight home game, topping Texas Southern 69-59 on Saturday. Gerard Andrus added 23 points and Faite Williams had six rebounds for Prairie View (12-11, 8-2 Southwestern Athletic Conference). Texas Southern was held to a season-low 20 second-half points. Justin Hopkins had 13 points for the Tigers (10-13, 7-3). Divonte Lumpkin added 10 points. Tyrik Armstrong had 8 points, eight assists and eight steals. The Panthers evened the season series against the Tigers with the win. Texas Southern defeated Prairie View 71-67 on Jan. 11. Prairie View takes on Grambling State at home next Saturday. Texas Southern plays Jackson State at home next Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
